Manager of Data Analytics, Community Safety and Well-Being - INF003850

Employment Type: Non-Perm Out-of-Scope
Location(s): SK-Rgna-Regina
Ministry: 003 Justice
Salary Range: $7049 - $9165 Monthly
Salary Supplement: 12%
Grade: MCP.07.

The Community Safety and Well-Being (CSWB) Branch of Integrated Justice Services is a fast-paced work environment that supports several key strategic portfolios under the Ministry of Justice and Attorney General and Ministry of Corrections, Policing and Public Safety. Our Branch is seeking a dynamic, influential, and flexible big-picture-thinker for the position of Manager Data Analytics – Community Safety and Well-Being.

In a matrix reporting structure to both a Director of Community Safety and Well-Being and the Director of Business Intelligence and Data Analytics, your primary responsibility will be acting as Community Safety and Well-Being’s data analytics strategist, thinker, leader, self-starter and collaborator. Your primary responsibilities will include the following:

Providing leadership, guidance, and supervision to team members of the CSWB data team by establishing team priorities and ensuring prompt and accurate completion of projects and activities.
Collaborating with business resources, community stakeholders and CSWB leadership to support and share data that can be leveraged to improve community safety and well-being;
Leading stakeholder engagement with agencies and communities on CSWB business intelligence strategies and approaches;
Filling a pivotal role in designing, developing, and managing data-sharing agreements with other ministries, agencies, and communities;
Developing a network across Human Services ministries and communities that support data sharing through community safety and well-being planning;
Having ongoing oversight of the Community Safety and Well- Being Branch’s information management, analytics, and business intelligence needs. This includes playing a lead role in the delivery of projects related to business intelligence;
Developing branch policies, practices and strategies related to geospatial display tools, data storage, and data accessibility in partnership with the ministry’s Strategic Systems and Innovation (SSI) Branch; and
Following and ensuring alignment of any new and existing data standards, data privacy procedures and policies (including CSWB Branch’s processes) to established ministry standards, policies, and procedures.

This position will identify and anticipate emerging issues, perform risk assessments and lead solution development in relation to branch and ministerial strategic policy and the development conceptual and theoretical frameworks. This position will act as a change agent, consulting with management, various levels of governments and communities to transform how Data analytics is leveraged to improve community safety and well-being in Saskatchewan.

We encourage candidates with a variety of backgrounds to apply, our candidate of choice will be able to quickly adapt to the level of technical expertise in the room and possess superior leadership and interpersonal skills. You will have both strong technical/data and behavioral competencies including:

Extensive knowledge of data management tools and processes, trends in open data, and analytics;
Extensive knowledge of and experience with data mining, pattern matching, data visualization, predictive modelling, and other analytics tools;
Extensive knowledge of organizational behavior, change management;
The ability to think laterally and use creativity and best practices for solutions with business outcome focus;
The ability to select appropriate research methodologies and apply statistical and analytical techniques supporting policy development, program administration and the development of strategies to measure, evaluate programs, and report on performance;
The ability to be diplomatic and tactful professional and take into account sector sensitivities and resolves issues through influence, persuasion, analysis or otherwise reconciling divergent views/interests;
The ability to establish credibility with a variety of audiences and maintain effective working relationships with colleagues and external stakeholders; and
Facilitate focus groups, working groups, and produce surveys gathering information from both leadership and technical audiences.

Typically, candidates would obtain this knowledge through graduate studies related to public policy, data science, or Computer Science with concentration in Business and experience working with community stakeholders or an equivalent combination of related experience and training. A salary supplement of up to 12% may be provided to a candidate that demonstrates exceptional credentials for the role.

We are committed to workplace diversity.

Hours of Work: M - Monthly Out of Scope
Number of Openings: 1

Closing Date: Jul 29, 2023, 12:59:00 AM

JOB DESCRIPTION

Applied ML Scientist, Health

POSITION OVERVIEW

As an Applied ML Scientist - Health, you will provide technical leadership and contribute to focused research breakthroughs and applications to solve real-world health problems with machine learning and AI. You will provide guidance and work with some of the best and brightest data scientists and machine learning (ML) engineering staff from leading industry and health organizations. You will collaborate with some of the leading machine learning researchers, data scientists and AI engineering teams. Publishing research papers on applied research is a part of this role, but the greatest focus is on the impact of applications, not on the quantity or quality of publications. We are seeking a scientist with research experience in Responsible AI in a deep learning context. Experience in Fairness, Explainability, Privacy, AI Safety, Recommender Systems, and Natural Language Processing are all valuable areas of knowledge for this role. This position is an individual contribution position and focused on providing technical leadership in implementation focused applied ML in health settings.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Lead research and implementation of varied machine learning and deep learning techniques in the health domain;
Work in collaboration with Vector’s Health team, and health sector partners to identify challenges in the health domain that can be solved using advanced ML techniques such as NLP, Computer Vision, Generative Models etc.;
Provide technical guidance to AI Engineering team members and lead delivery of applied ML projects in health;
Provide scientific advice regarding overall machine learning application strategies and roadmaps for the health domain;
Work in collaboration with Researchers, Machine learning specialists, and Vector affiliates to build demos, minimum viable products (MVP), reference implementations, and prototypes;
Provide scientific oversight for Vector-led or co-led efforts to prepare and present machine learning research in the health domain;
Serve as the lead Vector scientific contributor for health, including contributing to or leading the authoring of peer-reviewed research papers;
Contribute to training sessions and other initiatives for Vector’s professional staff and stakeholders that help increase AI knowledge and capacity of the health system to recognize and act on opportunities to apply machine learning;
Serve as an expert and facilitate identification of experts among Vector’s research community for external stakeholders to advise on machine learning research trends and applications;
Perform other functions as required e.g., providing scientific advice and technical support to other members of Vector’s leadership team and corporate projects led by Vector.

PROFILE OF IDEAL CANDIDATE

PhD degree in computer science or computer engineering with a research focus on machine learning required;
Demonstrated expertise in one or more of: ML for health, Explainable AI, AI Safety, privacy for AI/ML, AI governance, Nature Language Processing (NLP), Natural Language Understanding and generation;
Demonstrated experience applying machine learning research to novel problems and data sets;
Experience with software engineering and/or data engineering is considered an asset;
Strong knowledge and experience of Python;
Experience with parameter and architecture tuning of deep learning algorithms;
Experience using open source deep learning software frameworks (e.g, PyTorch, Tensorflow, JAX); and,
Experience with recommendation systems is considered an asset.

KEY SUCCESS MEASURES

Vector is successful in implementing its health strategy (including the strategic goal to support the widespread application of Health AI) and the industry sponsor retention strategy
Stakeholders that would otherwise be unable to utilize machine learning techniques are supported in identifying problems amenable to AI, and in utilizing machine learning
Following interactions with the Vector team, external stakeholders are positioned to perform, or secure external resources to perform, their own machine learning deployment independent of direct Vector involvement

THE OPPORTUNITY

Western Forest Products is hiring for a Timber Appraisal Data Analyst to join our team in Campbell River, BC.

What You’ll Do: As the Timber Appraisal Data Analyst, you are an integral member of our Timberlands financial process responsible for acquiring, processing and performing statistical analysis, translating complex data into strategies that support the Company to make better business decisions. You will analyze road and cutting permits, timber sale data, associated stumpage appraisal data, timber harvest data, and appraisal methodology ensuring Western delivers timely and accurate analysis, information, forecasts, submissions, and systems support in the most cost effective and efficient manner.

Who You Are: You come with 2-3 years of experience in data analyzing, combined with educational background in either Forestry, Business, Mathematics or Data Science with a focus on Data Analysis and Statistics. You have strong skills in analysis, data interpretation, database management and scripting languages. You’re proficient in a variety of statistical and reporting tools, including SPSS, SQL, Python, SAP Business Objects Infoview, and Power BI. You’re a critical thinker, a problem-solver, and an individual that’s eager to learn. Forestry experience is an asset to have, and new graduates from Data Analysis programs are welcome to apply!

Work Environment: We are proud to offer a flexible work environment. This position is based out of our Campbell River Office and will be a balance of work from home and in office based on the needs of the position.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Maintain databases and appraisal method configuration in enterprise application systems;
Analyze and report on the Company’s cutting permit (CP) stumpage adjustments impact;
Provide CP stumpage projections;
Acquire and validate Ministry CP stumpage determinations;
Perform financial analysis on harvest, log sales or log purchase options;
Perform financial impact analysis of Market Pricing System timber pricing options;
Provide Post Harvest Appraisal Data (PHADS) reappraisal accrual values; and
Track Post Harvest Appraisal Reconciliation Model (PHARM) status and Liability.
Lead maintenance of Appraisal Data System (Trimble CENFOR/LRM) and appraisal reporting systems;
Provide support to Timber Appraisals Team and other Western staff on Appraisal Data System (Internal and Ministry-ECAS, GAS, HBS) use to complete appraisal forms and produce appraisal reports.
Maintain cutting permit and road permit stumpage calculation spreadsheets;
Provide quarterly forecasts and final stumpage rate, average timber value, indicated rates and development cost reports for the operations;
Acquire and maintain reports and datasets from government contacts and systems (GAS, ECAS, HBS) reports and databases;
Maintain stumpage equation parameters in the Appraisal Data System, along with diagnosing problems users encounter;
Provide web reports and spreadsheets required for appraisal submissions under the Coast Appraisal Manual;
Monthly maintenance of stumpage rates in the Log Information Management Systems (LIMS);
Obtain and input PHADS into LIMS to support the PHARM Accrual Reporting process;
Provide forecast and final stumpage accrual rates to load into JRP Forest Ops (FOPS) to support Production Forecast process;
Receive and validate all stumpage determinations from the Ministry, distribute to submitter, indicating any discrepancies found;
Provide stumpage fee data, financial impact analysis, and advice for timber pricing, log sales/purchases, and harvest options;
Complete a parallel data collection, verification, and impact analysis of the timber sale data and equations used to annually update the Coast Market Pricing System in conjunction with Ministry through COFI and the joint Industry/Ministry Coast MPS Technical Subcommittee;
Provide support and troubleshooting for submitters uploading appraisal submissions into ECAS.

QUALIFICATIONS

Education and Experience

Degree in Business, Mathematics, Data Science or Forestry with an emphasis on Data Analysis and Statistics; or
Experience in the Forest Industry is an asset but not necessarily a requirement.

Skills, Knowledge and Required Competencies

Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and communicate significant amounts of complex information with attention to detail and accuracy;
Strong data analysis and interpretation capabilities, comfortable with interpreting statistics and completing regression analysis with statistical packages (SAS, GRETL, SPSS);
Working knowledge of databases (Oracle, SQL Server), scripting languages (SQL, R, PowerQuery M, Python)
Expertise to design and develop reporting (SAP Business Objects Infoview & Crystal Reports, Microsoft SSRS and Power BI) to illustrate forecasts, trends and correlations;
Expert level knowledge of Microsoft Office applications;
Competent in searching the internet for information; and
A critical thinker, problem solver, energetic, enthusiastic, and eager to learn.

YOUR CAREER

At Western Forest Products, we believe our most significant asset is our people. Investing in our people brings value and success to our business, ensuring a safe, engaged, productive and continuously improving workplace. We offer challenging opportunities working alongside the best in the industry to meet your career and professional development goals while providing competitive total rewards and recognition.

We provide a variety of on-the-job training and continuing education in many areas at Western to ensure you have the skills you need to succeed. Our promote-from-within culture recognizes high performance and we offer diverse career paths across the organization for those with the talent and will to advance.

Our total rewards offering including competitive pay, performance bonus, pension plan, benefits and other programs designed to support our employees.

WESTERN OVERVIEW

Western Forest Products is a leading forest products company that sustainably manages forests and manufactures high-quality wood products. Headquartered in Vancouver, British Columbia with operations in the coastal region of BC and Washington State, Western meets the needs of customers worldwide with a specialty wood products focus and diverse product offering.

Our commitment to health and safety, environmental stewardship and community engagement is core to how we do business at Western Forest Products.

Our approach to responsible business practices in all aspects of our business is multi-faceted. We adhere to and employ the most stringent environmental practices in the world. The steps we take to ensure the forests in which we operate are renewed and remain healthy and viable for future generations are mirrored in the care we take to make certain our communities continue to grow and prosper. This includes investing in communities where we operate and continuing to forge mutually beneficial relationships with First Nations in respect of their local and cultural interests.

